on: suburban spaces; the Cold War and its impact on young people; ethnicity, “race,” and work; the importance of play and recreation; children’s bodies, health and sexuality; and "the night," resistances and delinquency. Reinforced throughout this manuscript is the fact that children and adolescents were not only affected by their suburban experiences, but that they influenced the adult world in which they lived. Oral histories from former community members and archival materials, including school-based publications, form the backbone for a study that demonstrates that suburban life was diverse and filled with rich experiences for youngsters.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 06. Mrz 2024) 0aBaby boom generationzAlbertazCalgaryxHistoryy20th century. 0aSuburban lifezAlbertazCalgaryxHistoryy20th century. 4aCultural Studies. 4aHistory: Canadian History. 7aHISTORY / Canada / Post-Confederation (1867-).2bisacsh  aAlberta.  aBanff Trail.  aCalgary.  aCold War.  aFifties.  aSixties.  aadolescence.  aadolescents.  aatomic bomb.  ababies.  ababy boomer.  aboom.  achildhood history.  achildhood.  achildren.  acommunity.  adelinquency.  aeducation.  afamily.  aoral history.  apostwar.  aresistance.  aschool.  asuburbia.  asuburbs.  ateenagers.  aurban.  ayouth.08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertACUP Complete eBook-Package 2021z978311127221408iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertACUP Upgrade eBook-Package 2021z978311127464540uhttps://doi.org/10.51644/978177112501740uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9781771125017423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9781771125017/original  a978-3-11-127221-4  ACUP Complete eBook-Package 2021b2021  a978-3-11-127464-5  ACUP Upgrade eBook-Package 2021b2021  aGBV-deGruyter-alles